> This burger stacks up against the best, literally: Each bun holds a turkey patty that's been smothered in melted pepper jack cheese AND sautéed peppers and onions. Just in case that doesn't make this burger a front-runner for first-place, let's introduce the secret weapon: a special spicy ketchup with hot sauce that you can add to taste. If you aren't blown away yet, you will be when you're holding this bad boy in your hands.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounces} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Long Green Pepper{1} into strips.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Ketchup{2%tablespoon} and @Hot Sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%tablespoon}, half the @Sweet and Smoky BBQ Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}(to taste). (You'll use the rest of the BBQ Seasoning later.)

Roast on top rack, flipping halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and green pepper. Cook, stirring, until browned and softened, ~{7-9%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, combine @Ground Beef{10%ounces}, remaining BBQ Seasoning, and a big pinch of salt and pepper. (TIP: Wet hands first to prevent sticking.) Form into two ½-inch-thick rounds.

Set aside half the @Pepper Jack Cheese{½%cup}.

Divide remaining pepper jack between the center of each patty. Fold edges of meat around cheese, shaping and sealing to create cheese-stuffed patties, each slightly wider than a burger bun. Season all over with salt and pepper.

> Swap in beef for turkey.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook through, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

In the last 1-2 minutes of cooking, top each patty with a layer of veggies (you may have some left over), then top with reserved pepper jack; cover pan to melt cheese.

While patties cook, halve and toast @Potato Buns{2}.

Spread cut sides of buns with spicy ketchup. Fill buns with smothered patties and any remaining hot sauce if desired.

Divide burgers between plates and serve with potato wedges and any remaining veggies on the side.